parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETM can cause the vehicle to stall, surge, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

surges
or loses power; the engine RPMs fluctuate; the vehicle hesitates or lurches forward; the throttle pedal feels soft or spongy; the vehicle dies while driving.

surges

symptoms: The vehicle stalls
surges

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body or ETM (Electronic Throttle Module) can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies
often at low speeds
and may restart after turning off and on again. The "Performance Reduced" message may appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine temperature gauge rises rapidly
and the "High Engine Temp" message may appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The brake warning light illuminates
and the brakes may feel spongy or unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a loss of power to various systems, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The "Low Battery Voltage" message may appear on the dashboard
and the car may stall or die.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air mass sensor can cause the engine to stall or run poorly, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies
and the "Check Engine" light may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause a loss of power and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
and the car may stall or die.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETM can cause the engine to stall or surge, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or surges
the car loses power
the throttle pedal feels soft or spongy
the car hesitates or jerks when accelerating
and warning lights or messages appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the car to catch fire, leading to a risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The car catches fire
smoke appears from under the hood
and warning lights or messages appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag and SRS system can cause the airbags to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy in the event of an accident, leading to a risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light appears on the dashboard
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
and warning messages appear on the dashboard.
